# Rate Limiting Configuration Template

## Copy these to your .env file and adjust as needed

```env
# ======================================
# RATE LIMITING CONFIGURATION
# ======================================

# Requests per second per device
RATE_LIMIT_PER_SECOND=10

# Requests per minute per device
RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=300

# Requests per hour per device
RATE_LIMIT_PER_HOUR=3600

# Burst allowance multiplier (allows brief spikes)
RATE_LIMIT_BURST_ALLOWANCE=1.5

# Time window for rate limit cleanup (ms)
RATE_LIMIT_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=3600000

# ======================================
# REQUEST QUEUE CONFIGURATION
# ======================================

# Maximum concurrent requests per device
QUEUE_MAX_CONCURRENT_PER_DEVICE=2

# Maximum queue size per device
QUEUE_MAX_SIZE=100

# Request timeout in milliseconds
QUEUE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=30000

# Queue cleanup interval (ms)
QUEUE_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=3600000

# ======================================
# RACE CONDITION HANDLER CONFIGURATION
# ======================================

# Lock timeout in milliseconds
LOCK_TIMEOUT=30000

# Maximum retry attempts
LOCK_MAX_RETRIES=3

# Base retry delay in milliseconds (uses exponential backoff)
LOCK_RETRY_DELAY=100

# Lock cleanup interval (ms)
LOCK_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=3600000

# ======================================
# OPTIONAL: ROUTE-SPECIFIC OVERRIDES
# These are JSON strings for route-specific limits
# ======================================

# Authentication endpoints (stricter)
RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_LOGIN_PER_SECOND=2
RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_LOGIN_PER_MINUTE=20
RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_REGISTER_PER_SECOND=1
RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_REGISTER_PER_MINUTE=10

# Bulk operations (moderate)
RATE_LIMIT_BULK_UPSERT_PER_SECOND=5
RATE_LIMIT_BULK_UPSERT_PER_MINUTE=50

# Read operations (generous)
RATE_LIMIT_READ_PER_SECOND=20
RATE_LIMIT_READ_PER_MINUTE=500

# ======================================
# MONITORING & LOGGING
# ======================================

# Log rate limit violations
LOG_RATE_LIMIT_VIOLATIONS=true

# Log queue metrics
LOG_QUEUE_METRICS=true

# Log lock operations
LOG_LOCK_OPERATIONS=true

# Memory usage warning threshold (bytes)
MEMORY_WARNING_THRESHOLD=1073741824

```

## Application Code Integration

If using environment variables, update `src/index.js` or middleware initialization:

```javascript
// src/middlewares/rateLimitMiddleware.js - Update configuration
import { rateLimiter } from './rateLimitMiddleware.js';

// Apply env variables
if (process.env.RATE_LIMIT_PER_SECOND) {
  rateLimiter.config.requestsPerSecond = 
    parseInt(process.env.RATE_LIMIT_PER_SECOND);
}

if (process.env.RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE) {
  rateLimiter.config.requestsPerMinute = 
    parseInt(process.env.RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE);
}

// ... similar for other settings
```

